An Act facilitating the appropriation and expenditure of community preservation funds for
community housing purposes in the town of Chatham.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 1: Notwithstanding the definition of “moderate income housing” set forth in the
2 fifteenth paragraph of section 2 of chapter 44B of the Massachusetts General Laws, the Town of
3 Chatham, upon recommendation of its community preservation committee, may appropriate and
4 expend community preservation funds for purposes of community housing for those persons and
5 families whose annual income is less than 200 per cent of the area-wide median income.
6 Section 2: This act shall take effect upon passage.
